WITNESSES REPORTED THAT DURING TAKEOFF, THE GLIDER WAS BEING TOWED 
WHEN IT RELEASED AT APPROXIMATELY 300 FEET AGL AND ENTERED A LEFEET TURN. THE TURN 
CONTINUED, THE BANK ANGLE INCREASED AND THE GLIDER SUBSEQUENTLY HIT THE 
GROUND APPROXIMATELY 1 MILE SOUTHWEST OF THE ARPT. IMPACT OCCURRED IN A STEEP 
NOSE DOWN, LEFT WING LOW ATTITUDE. WITNESSES REPORTED THAT A RIGHT 
TURN WAS THE STANDARD PROCEDURE AFTER A RELEASE FROM A TOW. NO 
EVIDENCE OF A PREIMPACT MALFUNCTION OF THE GLIDER WAS FOUND, BUT ITS 
TOW HOOK WAS NOT LOCATED. THE TOW ROPE AND TOW HOOK ON THE TOW PLANE 
WERE EXAMINED AND NO DISCREPANCIES WERE NOTED. RESULTS OF MEDICAL AND 
TOXICALOGICAL EXAMS WERE NEGATIVE. 
